<subSubSection id="5FF065107D19FFE165ADFDB0FDD1AFFD" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="1755369B7D19FFE165ADFDB0FDD1AFFD" blockId="6.[151,1436,447,940]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis id="259EEA897D19FFE165ADFDB0FEB0AEDD" bold="true" box="[199,321,627,652]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" reason="1">
<emphasis id="259EEA897D19FFE165ADFDB0FECBAEDD" bold="true" box="[199,314,627,652]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Diagnosis</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
This poorly known species shares the dark stripe that partially covers the mesepimeron (posthumeral stripe) with 
<taxonomicName id="D0EA4D187D19FFE164E9FD5AFE04AEE1" authorityName="Machado" authorityYear="2006" box="[387,501,664,688]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracile">
<emphasis id="259EEA897D19FFE164E9FD5AFE04AEE1" box="[387,501,664,688]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">H. gracile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="D0EA4D187D19FFE16747FD5AFD4FAEE1" authorityName="Machado" authorityYear="2006" box="[557,702,664,688]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luizfelipei">
<emphasis id="259EEA897D19FFE16747FD5AFD4FAEE1" box="[557,702,664,688]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">H. luizfelipei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Figs. 31A, 31E, 32A); differs from these two species by having dorsal part of head much darker. Shares posterior lobe of prothorax orange without dark marks with 
<taxonomicName id="D0EA4D187D19FFE1604DFD7EFA6DAE85" authorityName="Machado" authorityYear="2006" box="[1319,1436,700,724]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracile">
<emphasis id="259EEA897D19FFE1604DFD7EFA6DAE85" box="[1319,1436,700,724]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">H. gracile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Figs. 31C, 32C). Differs from 
<taxonomicName id="D0EA4D187D19FFE1649CFD22FD76AEA9" authorityName="Machado" authorityYear="2006" box="[502,647,736,760]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luizfelipei">
<emphasis id="259EEA897D19FFE1649CFD22FD76AEA9" box="[502,647,736,760]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">H. luizfelipei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having dorsum of S2 pale (darker in 
<taxonomicName id="D0EA4D187D19FFE1613BFD22FB13AEA9" authorityName="Machado" authorityYear="2006" box="[1105,1250,736,760]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luizfelipei">
<emphasis id="259EEA897D19FFE1613BFD22FB13AEA9" box="[1105,1250,736,760]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">H. luizfelipei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="D0EA4D187D19FFE16073FD22FA7AAEA9" authorityName="Machado" authorityYear="2006" box="[1305,1419,736,760]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracile">
<emphasis id="259EEA897D19FFE16073FD22FA7AAEA9" box="[1305,1419,736,760]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">H. gracile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Cercus in lateral view: dorsobasal expansion present. Ventrobasal expansion very small but present. almost straight (Fig. 12B). Cercus in mediodorsal view: basal, medial and apical portions of cercus subequal. Ventral expansion with long hairs covering ventral 1/4. Ventral branch of medial process bluntly triangular with apex emarginate, sclerotized ridge splitting ventral branch in two, dorsal branch small, triangular and attached to sclerotized ridge by internal side of triangle (Fig. 12A).
</paragraph>
